params.configurator_: The address with authority to configure rewards.
params.duration_: The duration (in seconds) for which the rewards will run.
params.fToken2_: The address of the associated fToken contract 2, optional.
params.fToken3_: The address of the associated fToken contract 3, optional.
params.fToken_: The address of the associated fToken contract.
params.rewardAmount_: The total amount of underlying assets to be distributed as rewards.
params.startTime_: The timestamp when rewards are scheduled to start; must be 0 or a future time.
params.startTvl_: The TVL threshold below which the reward rate is 0.

getConfig().details: initiator_ is actually the configurator who has access to manage the rewards. named as is for backwards-compatibility reasons.

params.totalAssets_: amount of assets in the lending

returns.ended_: flag to signal that rewards have ended (always 0 going forward)
returns.rate_: rewards rate percentage per year with 1e12 RATE_PRECISION, e.g. 1e12 = 1%, 1e14 = 100%
returns.startTime_: start time of rewards to compare against last update timestamp

transitionToNextRewards().details: Note triggering this is not required for queued rewards to start accruing as that happens anyway in the `getRate`         view method, but it cleans up the status here in storage and gas optimizes the `getRate()` call.

FTOKEN().notice: address of the fTokens where these rewards are supposed to be set

constructor.notice: Sets variables for rewards rate configuration based on input parameters.

getConfig().notice: Returns config constants for rewards rate model

queueNextRewards(uint256,uint256).notice: queues next rewards which can be come active after current ongoing rewards.

startRewards(uint256,uint256,uint256).notice: start new rewards. LendingRewards must be an auth at the LendingFactory! set startTime set to 0 for using block.timestamp

transitionToNextRewards().notice: transitions to next queued rewards after current ongoing rewards ended. Callable by anyone.
